9.12.18  7:13 pm   Is there such a thing as originality?

     sure

     or are the ideas in art that we usually think are original just a hodgepodge of others' ideas that we've collected over time?

     there is a third ingredient, dodge, which you may be forgetting

     Is it disingenuous to use elements of other people's art in your own art?

     or to make it more interesting, find the elements their art had taken from other art, and mix those elements in too

     this has been tripping me up for a while because whenever i sit down make some art, i can only think to combine things i've seen.

     the more things you see, the smaller the parts you can combine, and combine parts from more things. if you combine 5 or more things you can't get in trouble. and if you combine 33 things, then the result will definitely be 'original'
